I live right across the street from this Jiffy Lube, and have been there quite a few times with my car.
As a girl, I usually am very hesitant to go anywhere near car dealerships or mechanics or anyone who has to deal with my car for fear that they will try to up sell me on stupid bullshit I don't need or scare me into buying some completely useless crap.
Having said that, I was relieved to find out that that is not the case at this Jiffy Lube.
The guys are all burly men, but they are decent and friendly and always do a good job.
I would definitely reccommend going here for an oil change if you just want to get it done quickly and get on with your life.

I always avoid getting my cars lubed and oil changed, because (1) it is inconvenient, and (2) the high pressure sales efforts.
After reading Krashawnda N's review of this Jiffy Lube, I thought I would give it a try.
It was kind of a last minute decision, as I wanted to get it done before I left on vacation, so I wouldn't have to do it when I got back.
They immediately got me in, and checked the car.
Surprisingly, they had my van in the data base - apparently a previous owner had used Jiffy.
Once we got that straightened out, it was fairly quick and easy.
I knew what I wanted, and there were no high pressure tactics - they were happy to do just what I requested.
They were very pleasant.
There was one glitch - apparently one of the fittings was difficult to get to - and it took a while longer than they expected.
But they explained it to me, apologized, and kept me informed of the progress.
All in all a very good experience.

As a single girl who knows nothing about cars and HATES going to the dealership (cuz they always rip me off), I take my car here ALL THE TIME.
I love that they don't ever try to screw me; they fix what needs to be fixed and leave the rest alone.
They are honest: they told me I don't need a new air filter...yet, and they are funny and nice.
They even humored me when I stopped in to have air put in my tires....I know, I know, I'm a grown woman, I should know how to do this.
Blah blah blah, the truth is, I know how....I just would rather have someone else do it for me;).
I have been coming here since I got my driver's liscense and will continue to come back because I appreciate not being swindled and taken advantage of and they do a great job for a reasonable price.
Keep it up, guys!

I recently leased my first new car in 12 years.
The dealership told me to have my first service performed at 5,000 miles, so I stopped in here to get it done.
The mechanic took a look at it, came back 5 minutes later, and asked me if I was aware that my car didn't need its first service until 7,500 miles.
I was not aware!
He still checked my fluid levels for free, sent me on my way, and told me to come back after another 2500 miles.
I definitely will.

